“As the Lakeman’s bare head was just level with the planks, the Captain and 
his posse leaped the barricade, and rapidly drawing over the slide of the 
scuttle, planted their group of hands upon it, and loudly called for the 
steward to bring the heavy brass padlock belonging to the companionway. Then 
opening the slide a little, the Captain whispered something down the crack, 
